properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 6 at 4:10AM EST until January 7 at 11:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, west winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts
up to 35 kt and waves 6 to 9 feet occurring. For the Gale
Watch, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
waves 7 to 10 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Superior from Saxon Harbor WI to Upper Entrance
to Portage Canal MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border
including Isle Royale National Park.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 11 AM EST this morning. For
the Gale Watch, from late tonight through Tuesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
